dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , [planimetry and contours] by U.S. Geological Survey. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: New Bellsville, Indiana. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3762 II NE. Type C--AMS 1. "A.M.S. Series V851" "Transverse Mercator projection." Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, and natural features. "Contour interval 10 feet." Marginal maps: Index to boundaries.--Index to adjoining sheets. "Planimetry by stereophotogrammetric (multiplex) methods by the U. S. Geological Survey, 1946. Countours by plane-table methods by the U. S. Geological Survey 1947. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS. Aerial photography August 1939. Public Land Surevey lines are based on the Second Principal Meridian and Base Line." "N3907.5-W8600/7.5." "Type C (AMS 1), 1947." "7-48."
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, 1948.
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army Map Service; Geological Survey (U.S.)
